# Quality Gates (Harness Engineering)

Execute these commands before and after every code change. They should be copy-pasteable for immediate execution.

## 1. Fast Health Check — Static Analysis
```bash
dart analyze
```
> Must have 0 warnings and 0 errors to pass.

## 2. Auto-Fix (dart fix)
```bash
dart fix --apply
```
> Batch apply all auto-fixable analysis warnings.

## 3. Code Formatting
```bash
dart format .
```
> Do not commit if any file has formatting issues.

## 4. Run Tests
```bash
# Test specific module (example: epub)
flutter test test/features/epub/

# Run all tests
flutter test
```

## 5. Coverage Gate
```bash
flutter test --coverage
# Verify results in: coverage/lcov.info
```

## 6. One-Command Quality Gate (CI Simulation)
```bash
dart analyze && dart format --set-exit-if-changed . && flutter test && echo "ALL GATES PASSED"
```
> Do not commit unless this command succeeds.

---

## Pre-Commit Checklist (Execute in Order)
```
[ ] dart fix --apply            (Auto-fix)
[ ] dart analyze                (Zero analysis errors)
[ ] dart format .               (Formatting verification)
[ ] flutter test <target>       (Relevant tests pass)
[ ] Fail-Check performed        (Verify tests fail when code is damaged)
[ ] flutter test --coverage     (Check coverage status)
[ ] git diff --stat             (Final review of changes)
```

